    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">2pt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">IA combined</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>When placing IA words on the board, prioritise positions where the higher-value letter (I at 1 points) lands on a premium square. A double-letter score on I adds 1 extra points, while a triple-letter placement adds 2 extra. Look for open lanes where you can extend existing words by threading IA through intersecting tiles already on the board.</p>

<p>In the mid-game, holding IA together gives you flexibility because this combination appears in words across multiple length categories — from short tactical plays to seven-letter bingos. If your rack contains IA plus common tiles like E, R, S, or T, check for bingo possibilities before settling for a shorter word. The extra 50-point bonus for using all seven tiles often outweighs a high-scoring five-letter alternative.</p>

